entry.title: Video: Support Dolby Vision downgrade playback for MSE
entry.content:
For now, if Chrome wants to implement Dolby Vision support, platform

decoders like `D3D11VideoDecoder` or `VideoToolboxVideoDecoder` won't

work. On macOS AVFoundation is required and on Windows MediaFoundation

is required to support such format from what I understand.



Regarding the above issues, as Dolby Vision contents usually

encoded with H.264/5 codecs, then as long as device supports H.264/5 codec and `dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id` equals to 1,2,4 (HDR10,

SDR,HLG compatible), then a downgrade should be performed and let

these videos at least able to playback normally as H.264/5 codec

contents as long as developer `addSourceBuffer` with mimetype

looks like `hev1.2.4.L120.90` or `avc1.4d4015`.



Note that when `addSourceBuffer` with mimetype looks like `dvh1.08.07`,

then dolby vision contents will always be treated as dolby vision,

the playback may still fails as expected if browser doesn't

support dolby vision on the current platform.



For web developers, the logic will be something like below:



```

if (isTypeSupported('video/mp4;codecs="dvh1.08.07"')) {

if (use_rpu) {

// Should be success and rendered with RPU meta.

source.addSourceBuffer('video/mp4;codecs="dvh1.08.07"');

...

} else if (dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 1 ||

dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 2 ||

dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 4) {

// Should be success and rendered without RPU meta as

// normal HLG/HDR10/SDR contents.

source.addSourceBuffer('video/mp4;codecs="hev1.2.4.L120.90"');

...

} else {

// Downgrade is not allowed, playback fails.

}

} else if (isTypeSupported('video/mp4;codecs="hev1.2.4.L120.90"')) {

if (dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 1 ||

dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 2 ||

dvcc.dv_bl_signal_compatibility_id === 4) {

// Should be success and rendered without RPU meta as

// normal HLG/HDR10/SDR contents.

source.addSourceBuffer('video/mp4;codecs="hev1.2.4.L120.90"');

...

} else {

// Downgrade is not allowed, playback fails.

}

} else {

// HEVC is not supported, playback fails.

}

```

entry.title: [enrollment] Do not auto-retry rollback enrollment.
entry.content:
crrev.com/c/3745584 made it so that rollback enrollment skips success

screen (as intended) and auto-retries on error (not intended).



The retry logic is not spamming due to a back-off timer, but is not

desired.



The user should decide themselves whether they want to retry or fallback

to manual enrollment.



Remove ambiguous IsAutomaticEnrollmentFlow().



Replace its use cases with explicit checks:

* Should auto-retry (only for Hands-off zero touch now).

* Should skip success message (Hands-off zero touch and rollback).

entry.title: Reland "Exclude HeuristicSource::kLegacy from non-active patterns"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 440828a02e56dcecd43896676a0c765db907c3b9



The CL removed "legacy" from the possible values of the feature

parameter kAutofillParsingPatternActiveSource. This broke a bunch of

parsing tests, since they are parameterized by pattern source. This CL

fixes this (see patchset 1 -> latest) by excluding "legacy" in

builds without Autofill internal patterns.



Presumably, this didn't show up during the CQ because none of the bots

are using the internal patterns.



Original change's description:

> Exclude HeuristicSource::kLegacy from non-active patterns

>

> A HeuristicSource describes a mechanism to get heuristic predictions,

> which is currently either ML or regexes. Due to pattern provider,

> which can provide different regex definitions, "regexes" is split

> further into different PatternSources.

>

> The active HeuristicSource defines the mechanism that's used to compute

> the fields' heuristic types used in production (the one that will

> influence the overall type used for filling).

>

> The non-active HeuristicSources are defined as the set of all available

> HeuristicSources, except the active HeuristicSource. The PatternSources

> among these non-active HeuristicSources are used to compute shadow predictions for the kAutofillParsingPatternProvider experiment.

>

> What exactly all available HeuristicSources are depends on build flags

> and feature flags, and this CL changes that definition.

>

> Generally:

> - HeuristicSource::kMachineLearning is only available when

> kAutofillModelPredictions is enabled.

> - HeuristicSource::kDefault, HeuristicSource::kExperimental and

> HeuristicSource::kNextGen are only available in Chrome branded builds

> when kAutofillParsingPatternProvider is enabled.

> - HeuristicSource::kLegacy is always available.

>

> This CL removes HeuristicSource::kLegacy from the available patterns in

> Chrome branded builds when kAutofillParsingPatternProvider is enabled.

> This is desirable for a few reasons:

> - Chrome branded builds with kAutofillParsingPatternProvider are not

> using the kLegacy patterns, not even for shadow metrics. They are

> intended to be lower-quality regexes for non-Chrome branded builds.

> - Since they are currently part of the non-active HeuristicSources,

> they take up additional computational resources during parsing.

>

entry.title: [gardener] Revert "Cleanup network::mojom::URLResponseHead"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 9c9653781023db9bbd86c2e873bffdcbaae25e28.



Reason for revert:

I think this is causing MSan failures, e.g.

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20ChromiumOS%20MSan%20Tests/39949



->

#0 0x55d134f77a97 in blink::ResourceFetcher::HandleLoaderFinish(blink::Resource*, base::TimeTicks, blink::ResourceFetcher::LoaderFinishType, unsigned int) ./../../third_party/blink/renderer/platform/loader/fetch/resource_fetcher.cc:2105:9



is accessing

if (resource->GetResponse().ShouldPopulateResourceTiming())



which seems uninitialized since this CL.



Original change's description:

> Cleanup network::mojom::URLResponseHead

>

> While investigating https://crbug.com/1507770 I noticed two things:

> 1. ct_policy_compliance is not used any more.

> - ct_policy_compliance was introduced by https://crrev.com/534288.

> - It is not used after https://crrev.com/957351.

> 2. web_bundle_url is used only checking if the response is an inner

> response of a WebBundle.

>

> So we can remove ct_policy_compliance param, and replace web_bundle_url

> param with a new bool param.

>

> The size of network::mojom::URLResponseHead decreases from 1072 bytes to

> 944 bytes.

>

entry.title: Use default comparison operators in base::StrongAlias.
entry.content:
For a defaulted operator<=> of a struct to derive its return type (i.e.

std::strong_ordering, std::weak_ordering, or std::partial_ordering), the

struct's members need to implement operator<=> as well - otherwise

it defaults to operator<=>(...) = delete;



In the case of base::StrongAlias, this means that its UnderlyingType

needs to implement operator<=> if the resulting alias should have a

non-deleted operator<=>. Currently, there are two instances in the

code base that do not do that, blink::IdentifiableSurface and

absl::monostate.



This CL implements operator<=> for the former, while removing the

StrongAlias wrapping the latter.

entry.title: [mullet m3] Initialize trigger source in AED::OnQuery.
entry.content:
The Suggestion trigger source is part of the suggestion generation

request and is passed to BAM::OnAskForValuesToFillImpl. This trigger

source affects what type of suggestions will be generated for a given

form and field (manual fallback enables the users to generate address

and credit card suggestions on arbitrary forms). Thus the trigger

source must be set during query initialization. AED::OnQuery is

responsible for this initialization.



This CL sets the suggestion trigger source in AED::OnQuery.This makes

the trigger source passed to the AED::OnSuggestionsReturned unused.

The goal is to remove that parameter from

AED::OnSuggestionsReturned in the subsequent CLs.



This change requires every call to AED::OnSuggestionsReturned to be

preceded by a call to AED::OnQuery to initialize the suggestion query

with the correct trigger source. AED::OnSuggestionsReturned is used in:

* BAM::OnAskForValuesToFillImpl

* SingleFieldFormFillers

* BAM::RefetchCardsAndUpdatePopup



The first 2 do not override the trigger source. The trigger source is

overridden in BAM::RefetchCardsAndUpdatePopup. That's why a call to

AED::OnQuery is added in BAM::RefetchCardsAndUpdatePopup.



Next steps: remove `trigger_source` from AED::OnSuggestionsReturned.

entry.content:
Currently, there exists IPP (IP Protection) metrics that

measure the amount of traffic sent to and received from the proxies.

This is measured based on all parameters relevant to IPP being

applicable (e.g, tokens being retrievable, token cache not

being empty, etc).

the token logic is set up. This is vital to estimate the traffic

based on different candidate policies. This CL adds metrics to

measure the traffic sent to and received from proxies

based on the eligibility of traffic (match based on the MDL).
